Rating: 4
I love this cake. It's perfect if you are entertaining guests who are gluten-free and is a great addition to a Passover meal. It's also just wonderful if there are no dietary restrictions. I agree with other posters that the double boiler isn't necessary - just melt the butter and chocolate together over low heat and stir constantly. I also find that 20 minutes is enough baking time since carry-over cooking takes place in the pan after you remove the cake from the oven.

