Rating: 4
Judging from some of the negative comments about this recipe, I think some reviewers must be unaware of just what a flourless cake is supposed to be like. Rather than your typically light, fluffy layer-type cake or even a dense pound cake or carrot cake, a flourless cake is supposed to be thin (about 3/4 of an inch thick) and very dense, somewhat like a chewy brownie. This is an excellent yet very easily made version of the dessert. I prefer to dust it with sifted powdered sugar rather than cocoa before cutting the cake. Some people add 1/2 to 1 teaspoon of vanilla, and it might be good with chopped nuts, too. However, it's great without modification, especially if you're a chocolate lover, and especially when served with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream (or both).

Rating: 4
This was my first attempt at this recipe, and the results were phenomenal.It's not the most amazing flourless chocolate cake recipe I've ever had, but it was a smashing success, and a breeze to make. The only adjustments I'll make the next time is using a slightly smaller pan, as the final result did come out a bit thinner than I'd anticipated. But it was delicious and dense, and has quickly moved up in the ranks of chocolate cake recipes in this household!

