Rating: 4
This cake is fabulous! Made it in a 9" pan with these ingredient changes (thanks to previous reviews) - 6 oz. chocolate, 1 cup sugar, 5 eggs, and 3/4 cup cocoa. I also added 1/2 tsp. cayenne (cake had a bit of a spicy bite afterwards) - bake for 25 minutes. Followed recipe except made these changes - mixed egg yolks and sugar in separate bowl, added melted chocolate and butter to egg yolk/sugar mixture, whisked egg whites and folded into chocolate mixture. Last, used Trader Joe's Bittersweet Chocolate and Droste cocoa. Served with lightly sugared whipped cream. Cake was not too dense and a hit at a dinner party!

