Rating: 0
I'm not rating this recipe, as I didn't follow it as written. Instead, I took some of the reviewers' suggestions, some of which did not work well for me. First, be sure that you don't use chocolate that is *too* dark. I used half Valrhona 71% and half Valrhona 85%. In the future, I would probably use 60%, as (even though I adore dark chocolate) the resulting cake was just too bitter/chalky. Second, don't cut down on the sugar the first time that you make it. I used about 2/3c sugar instead of 3/4c, and (even though I habitually reduce the sugar in a recipe) it just didn't work quite right. Third, the texture of the cake was moist, but very crummy. I'm not sure how to fix that. I'd have preferred the brownie texture that other reviewers achieved. I did bake it for 20 minutes -- perhaps that was too long? In the end, I served the cake with a generous dollop of cocoa whipped cream (recipe from Joy of Cooking). This saved the cake from being a complete flop. In short, I would recommend trying the recipe as written the first time you make it.

