Rating: 4
Fantastic!!! This cake was devoured at my last dinner party. I used Ghiradelli chocolate in the cake, and topped it with a rich glaze made this way: boil half a cup of heaving whipping cream and half a cup of dark corn syrup. Remove from heat and stir in 9 ounces of finely chopped semisweet or bittersweet chocolate. Spread half of glaze on top and sides of cooled cake. Put cake in freezer for 3 minutes. Pour rest of glaze on top of cake. Allow to fully set in the refridgerator for one hour.

