This recipe is easy and delicious ! My father was asking for more. Everyone one at work just raved. I'm not a cake person, but I make this recipe alot. It is especially wonderful for chocoholics who are in a hurry but need to impress ! It always turns out great !

Rating: 3
I've made this several times and always get rave reviews from all my guests. I used the advice of one of the other cooks in the review who suggested cutting back the corn syrup, and it still turned out fine. Sometimes the cake cracks more than others, but even if it doesn't look stunning, it tastes so good that it doesn't really matter.

Rating: 3
This is an excellent recipe to convert those like me who are skeptical of most cake recipes. I thought it was deep, intense and satisfying in its flavor and texture, and I'd make it again for guests. I'd serve it with a raspberry coulis!

Rating: 4
This was fabulously easy and everyone loved it! I served it for New Year's dinner. VERY important to use a good quality chocolate; I used Hawaiian Vintage Chocolate (www.hawaiianchocolate.com) and everyone could tell that it was something special.

Rating: 4
Wonderfully quick and easy dessert which turns out decadently chocolate. Great with vanilla ice cream.

Rating: 4
This cake was very easy to make, however, it doesn't look pretty on top, even when inverted. I served this w/ a chocolate whipped cream. Next time I would make a chocolate glaze for the top to cover up the cracks.

Rating: 3
I made this dessert for Christmas Eve and it was a hugh success. I served it with whipped cream and a cranberry-raspbery sauce on the side to make it a little more festive. The cake was moist and delicious and I will make this again soon.

Rating: 3
I thought this turned out a little dry, but it could be my fault as I used a 9" cake pan rather than 8" pan. The top was very concave, so I filled with Cinnamon Whipped Cream. I also passed fresh strawberry sauce with it, so the slight dryness was really not a problem. Really very easy, and guests liked it. Served 8.

Rating: 4
This cake is as good as it is easy! It is moist, rich and served warm with ice cream or whipped cream....to die for! I would highly recommend making it for any special occasion.

Rating: 4
The flavour of this cake is wonderful! I'm a chocolate addict and there isn't a more chocolatey cake anywhere! However, because of its richness, I tended to think more along the lines of "brownies" and cut it up into squares and topped them with icing. As a cake, or as brownies, this cake is a must!

Rating: 4
My husband made this for my Birthday. Probably the 1st thing he ever baked. It was out of this world, everyone loved it. The most decadent chocolate cake I ever had. This is now my mandatory Birthday cake.

Rating: 3
This was very easy to make and tasted delicious. I definitely plan to make it again. Next time I won't invert it though -- why serve the ugly side up? I sifted powdered sugar over the end product and served it with cinnamon whipped cream. Yummy!

Rating: 4
This is one of the best and easiest flourless chocolate cakes that I have ever made. I have made it a number of times and receive rave reviews every time I have made it.